In this context, the amendment No. 19posle 2004 concerning intergovernmental administrative assistance for the recovery of certain claims was adopted.
A new authoritative piece of legislation was enacted by Commission Regulation (EC) No 1179/2008 of 28 November 2008.
The annexes to this regulation contain new application forms to be used from 1 January 2009. Furthermore, the Regulation makes the electronic transmission mandatory and obliges the requesting authority to certify the conformity of all documents sent to the respective original.
Key principles of international administrative assistance on the recovery of claims are:
1. The principle of reciprocity applies;
2. Administrative assistance must only be provided on request and if all conditions are met;
3. Administrative assistance does not extend to claims deemed to be a criminal sanction in the requested State;
4. The procedure of intergovernmental administrative assistance for the recovery of claims must be carried out in accordance with the national law of the requested State;
5. In the recovery process, foreign receivables do not take precedence over domestic receivables;
6. Administrative assistance is provided only to recover undisputed claims;
7. The principle of exploitation applies: The requesting state must use all means to recover the claim, which is due to it under national law.
Law No. 19posous 2004 provides for three forms of administrative assistance: The provision of information, the provision of legal acts and the actual recovery.
