5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two Court of Auditors has proved its worth.
This has provided the necessary insights into the systems used in both countries: In particular: • Intra-Community turnover, • risk management at the VAT, in particular with regard to the selection of risky sales, • recovery VAT receivables and • VAT audit of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and the systems outlined above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to stimulate discussion among interested bodies about what audit approaches and strategies can be used to combat fraud. This applies, for example, to the relationship between and between Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and insights gained should encourage the cooperation of the administration of the United States to continue to be examined together.
